options
-------

Player: information for one player:
- id = identification number (a short)
- name
- level = levels for each blockset (vector of unspecified size)
- position of next box: left or right
- keys when playing alone, at the left, at the right.

It can read and write its contents from/to an istream/ostream in the
following format:

ID PLAYER_NAME
LEVEL0 LEVEL1 ...
LEFT/RIGHT_INDICATOR (`<' or `>')
KEYS_ALONE0 KEYS_ALONE1 ...
KEYS_LEFT0 KEYS_LEFT1 ...
KEYS_RIGHT0 KEYS_RIGHT1 ...

Empty lines and those starting with ; # % or / are ignored. Spacing is
not critical, but tabs ('\t') haven't been tested.


GlobalOpts: global options:
- default keys alone/left/right

It can read and write its contents from/to an istream/ostream in the
following format:

KEYS_ALONE0 KEYS_ALONE1 ...
KEYS_LEFT0 KEYS_LEFT1 ...
KEYS_RIGHT0 KEYS_RIGHT1 ...

More global options are likely to be added later.
